snippet.textDisplay: the production team was crafty in recreating the streets of Dhaka in Ahmedabad of India. The brilliant set designers did a mighty good job in recreating the rickshaws, wall arts, CNGs and small elements that mark the identity of the city. Only drone shot of Buriganga (the river) has the real glimpse of Dhaka.

Yooo Chris, Chrispy, C Dawg, Hemsy! You probs reading the comments, checking to see if we like your movie. Truth is, i havent seen it. All the comments arent exactly great tho.
Going by film history, if youre ever offered a role where the only big star is you, then probably give it a pass brother.
For example ...
Any jason statham movie
🤣.
I watched saving private ryan the other day and forgot how many names that film has in it. Only like 4 major ones, but still.
My favourite movie is the avengers infinity war. Came out like 3 years ago?? and im still shook every time i watch it.
I reckon you could do a castaway (tom hanks) type film. If theres ever been a one man movie ....i did just advise you to steer clear but this is a classic example of quality film making. So simple yet engaging and full of depth. You watch with intensity the whole film.
So my idea is....

Maybe a downed plane,
you're the only survivor,
things that WERENT ON THE PLANE begin washing ashore day by day.
You build your camp on this tropical island.
Find a message in a bottle BUT NEVER OPEN IT. (upon first handling it, you contemplate opening, but decide not to)
I can screenwrite this whole scene but i wont lol.
The major storyline revovles around the island being a government simulation and youre being watched on screens the whole time.
AND GUESS WHO IS YOUR GOVERNMENT MONITOR?
YOUR BROTHER!.
so theres no way of contacting you, cause youre on an island, so he secretly sends you survival items through simulation.


Who wants more????

Like this comment so chris can start making this movie for us 🤣🤙
